I hadn't even thought of it before @alkirahandmade's comment about sunflower seeds - they ARE all differently patterned! Like snowflakes of the ground:) I lined them all up today to check out the theory & then got lost in looking & playing around (hence the photo:)) I wonder what it is about establishing order & patterns that is so satisfying? I find that especially when my brain is racing I end up trying to point it in a useful direction like 'the 2nd draw' or some other devil's-nest area (except paper work - I never want to do that). I thought about the ceramicists that Ai WeiWei employed to make the 100 million handcrafted porcelain seeds (really!) that covered the floor of the Tate Modern - when did it cease to be therapeutic? About 1000 in perhaps? - - - - - #itellstories #sunflowerseed #aiweiwei #sunflowers #itellstoriesthroughobjects #garden #melbourne

Yes, by that point my band existed. But that night signalled a bit of a turning point for me. "In My Father's House" from the Ko e Hala Hangatonu: The Straight Path series (2013-2016) made with earth pigments, natural dyes, and tuitui (Candlenut soot) on ngatu (barkcloth) --- Elaborate geometry of pattern unfolded on raw barkcloth. Tongan ngatu is a special form of art collaboratively made by women, by beating the softened inner bark of a hiapo (paper mulberry tree), rubbing natural dyes, and highlighting the motifs with hand painting. --- I loved this because of how magnificent it was to look at. The intricate, detailed patterns are so authentic, and it's a lot coming from a mashup of tree bark, natural dyes, and many pairs of hands. There are many cultures and tribes in this world that can do a lot more than we realize, with stories we have yet to hear. And when a work of art is bigger than you, it gives way for you to see it as what it is: powerful.

Today I decided (stupidly) to go by MYSELF to Ikea with two kids.  In my defence there was an item I had wanted for a long time on sale at $200 off and there were only 4 in Stock so I had to work fast.  Everything was going OK. I had Leo in the Ergo and Finn was behaving. People had helped me put the boxes on my trolley and I felt I had that shit under control. I then got my car and started to pack the boxes in when I realised they weren't going to fit. WTF! totally didn't think of that and no amount of pushing and manoeuvring was going to get them in. IKEA do have delivery for something close to $100 and wouldn't hold my items for me to come back and collect the rest so I was in a predicament. The lady beside me then offered to drop them at my house as she lived close by.  I have to say what an f&cking legend. That lady could see I was starting to stress, she had kids so she understood and she was willing to take an extra load in her car and drive slightly out of her way to drop them off. I did not know her from a bar of soap but it's people like her that truly make the world a better place so thank you Alli!! To be honest the worst part of this was Leo screaming half of the way home in the car. I pulled over to feed him but still he screamed and it makes me so anxious listening to it that I start to lose my mind a little. Poor Finn just sat there listening to him cry and then started to cry as well.  So here I was stuck in traffic, car full of boxes, with two screaming kids in the back ğŸ˜‚ I am surprised I didn't start crying too.  Pass me a god damn wine. I'm happy to see the end of today! ğŸ·ğŸ¾ (and thank you to Finn for being a good boy! I don't know what I would have done if he was naughty as well)

Princes Park. What a night for a run and what a way to reward myself than drinking from my favourite water fountain. The water fountain that made me find my love for water fountains. With every step I took I yearned more for her crystal goodness. The desire became unbearable but I pushed on as I knew the longer I waited, the greater the sensation would be. I finished and approached the Goddess. Pressed her button to get my fix. Nothing. I couldn't believe it. My heart sank. How could the plumber have let this happen. I felt disgusted. It may sound obvious (or even silly) but first impressions really do count - especially in business. --- Like a first date, your first business meeting with a new prospect or potential client should be memorable. --- Pull out all the stops. Freshly cut flowers in your office or meeting space, great coffee or cold glass of water, some yummy treats to nibble on or even your favourite blend in an oil burner could be all it takes to turn a drab meeting into a fun one. Or, if you've opted to meet out, make sure you choose a space that serves great food or coffee, has some intimate or quiet areas where you can talk (and be heard) and is filled with natural or ambient light. It helps if the wait staff are friendly and the service is good too. --- These simple, yet significant touches will instantly set your client at ease and show them that you've been considerate of their needs even before you've done business with them. --- Granted this advice won't help you with your sales pitch - but that's a whole other post ğŸ˜‰ . . . . #meeting #meetings #clients #prospects #firstimpressions #sales #salespitch #businesswoman #business #businessadvice #b2b #b2c #agency #agencylife #strategy #strategygame #imaginecre8tiv #melbourne #marketing #content

Roti prata and Malaysian food for lunch. Prata was delicious (not too oily and just the right amount of flakiness and bite to it), Mee Goreng was really tasty (though the one at killiney earlier in the week had a better balance of flavours), and the Satay (though humongous) actually smelled authentic and tasted as close to the real thing amongst all the satays i've tried here so far. It's still no where near the taste of the satay that I grew up with, but it'll do. The ayam was fragrant and had a nice char to it, but out of the lot was my least fav.  That said, everything I've had today was nice.  #melbournefoodie #melbourneeats #melbournelife #melbourne #foodstagram #prata #roticanai #eattheworld #instafood #sundaybrunch #rotiroad

I remembered my experiences in high school and in life. And what I can say is, please, be kind to one another, we never know what's going on in someone else's life!  And given to the fact that the conception of right or wrong is different for each one of us, my message is clear... Doesn't matter who you are, just don't do to others what you wouldn't like them to do with you! Wish you all a life full of love!

This gem of deep fried goodness blew our minds, after talking to the owner we found out the place has been open for 44 years doing the same type of deep fried skewers and only being able to sit a maximum of 8 people at one time.  Watching her cook methodically, clean and entertain us as she was the only one the in the kitchen was simply amazing. Flinders station. The main station building, completed in 1909, is a cultural icon of Melbourne, with its prominent dome, arched entrance, tower and clocks one of the city's most recognisable landmarks. It is listed on the Victorian Heritage Register. The Melburnian saying "I'll meet you under the clocks" refers to the row of clocks above the main entrance, which indicate the time-tabled time of departure for trains on each line; another saying, "I'll meet you on the steps", refers to the wide staircase underneath these clocks. Flinders Street Station is responsible for two of Melbourne's busiest pedestrian crossings, both across Flinders Street, including one of Melbourne's few pedestrian scrambles.  #flinders #flindersstreets #melbourne #heritage #clocks #victorianheritage #visitmelbourne

This is today's made-up bedtime story I told my dog Milli.  What Milli Saw: Milli The Best Dog was troubled. It was wild, windy and wet outside. The tree out the front of the house was dancing like those big guys outside the car selling place with the gangly arms up and funny heads. So much dancing but just wind music. She was troubled because she was warm and cosy. She had a full tummy and a soft fleecy woobie (some people call them a security blanket). But nice, gentle Andrew with the sore eyes who lives outside Coles would be outside in the rain. So would Brendon who says hello to everyone and sleeps in the bookshop doorway. Milli was so sad. The next day she gathered all the hotel owners together and told them they had to give any unoccupied rooms to people and dogs and cats and animals except nasty rats. Everyone deserves a woobie. It was called the Milli Woobie Decree. #melbourne #story #doglover #doglife #dog #winter #homeless #australia

#authenticselfie  This weekend was a time of reflection with some of my closest friends. We drew a picture of ourselves and then passed it round and we all wrote what we love about each other. Then it came time to write about ourselves, and that's when it got hard for some of us. It was so easy to build each other up but society tells us we shouldn't think we are wonderful, we are full of ourselves if we do. I think knowing qualities that make us amazing is so empowering and let's us do good in this world. Only thinking negative thoughts about ourselves only hold us back. I challenge you to tell me what you like about you!

'HWY' is the second album from Melbourne rock band, Dave Wright & the Midnight Electric. After the release of their debut album,'The Lucky Country' in 2014, they entered SAE studios, South Melbourne,between August and October of last year and recorded 'HWY'. #HWY is a bona fide rock album. It's as simple as that. The album contains 8 songs as listed: 'Coming Home' 'Sweet Caroline' 'Where the Needle Hits the Red' 'Avenues of Honour' 'Happiness' 'Bigger than the Two of Us' 'Rain' 'HWY' There are too many highlights to mention here on this album.  However a couple that simply cannot be overlooked  include 'Avenues of Honour'. Written about the returned soldiers and avenues of trees planted in the fallen soldiers honour, this song may just prove to be a defining moment in Wright's career. 'HWY' is another exceptional song from the album. The song peaks with the guitar pairing of Wright and Robert Barber letting lose and cranking things up on their respective Rickenbacker and Fender Telecaster guitars. The album is available now on limited edition yellow/gold vinyl. It'll also be available in limited numbers on Record Store Day, coming up on April 22. The CD is also available now from independent music stores including Readings, Rocksteady Records in Melbourne and from RSD, Paradise Records in Brunswick,  If your forte is listening to albums that are made to be turned up loud and shared with your neighbours, then, 'HWY' is the album for you! @midnight_electric @timcavroxx @rosso_emperor @thatneilsalmon @johnbryant1196  #vinylnerd #vinylporn #vinylgeek #vinylcollection #vinyljunkie #colouredvinyl #indierock #vinylcollection #vinyljunkie #spin #vinycommunity #vinyloftheday #spinningvinyl #spinning #vinyloftheday #vinylgram #vinylrecords #turntables #vinyljunkies #vinylfreak #vinylporn #turntable #record #melbourne #rockmusic #rsd #rsd2017 #dwme #davewrightandthemidnightelectric
